history.content:
No, it doesn't.  Some students currently enrolled will change their mind.  It's possible new capacity might be added.  While by definition being on the waitlist means enrollment is not guaranteed and a backup plan is advised.

Note that waitlists for lower div classes (like 61B) are processed in order regardless of student status beginning after all undergrads have had their phase 2 appointment which already happened in December.

You are not enrolled now only because the lab and dis sections you have chosen are full.

There are a handful of labs and discussions that have space now; you can tell which sections have space on classes.berkeley.edu.  If you are willing to switch to attend a discussion and lab section that both have capacity, you would be enrolled today.

I am an incoming junior exchange student, currently #83 on the CS61B waitlist.

According to the policies, my enrollment will not be processed at Phase II (after Jan 9)

I see that there are already only 70 open seats left.

Does this mean that my chance of getting enrolled in CS61B is nearly zero?
